Measurement of electromagnetic shielding effectiveness (SE) Using a network analyser (N5222A; Agilent Technologies), we measured SE in a two-coaxial transmission line configuration. For this measurement, we grew the films on double-sided polished (0001)Al2O3 substrates (area: 22.8 × 10.1 mm2; thickness: 2 mm). The sample was positioned between two waveguides to measure the S parameters (S11 and S21) by emitting the electromagnetic wave from port 1. S11 was determined from the BLSO films by detecting the reflected wave at port 1. S21 was acquired by detecting the transmitted wave at port 2 through the films and Al2O3 substrate. The total SE was calculated by summing the contributions from absorption (SEA=10log1-S112S212\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
